&lt;h3 id=&#34;224-concurrency&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#224-concurrency&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;2.2.4&lt;/strong&gt; Concurrency&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;å¹¶å‘&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;23-the-rte-generator&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#23-the-rte-generator&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;2.3&lt;/strong&gt; The RTE Generator&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The RTE generator is one of a set of tools5 that create the realization of the AUTOSAR virtual function bus for an ECU based on information in the ECU Configuration Description. The RTE Generator is responsible for creating the AUTOSAR software component API functions that link AUTOSAR software-components to the OS and manage communication between AUTOSAR software-components and between AUTOSAR software-components and basic software modules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RTE ç”Ÿæˆå™¨æ˜¯åˆ›å»º VFB çš„å·¥å…·ï¼Œè´Ÿè´£ä¸Šä¸‹å±‚çš„äº¤äº’&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;24-design-decisions&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#24-design-decisions&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;2.4&lt;/strong&gt; Design Decisions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;3-rte-generation-process&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#3-rte-generation-process&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;3 RTE Generation Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The RTE Generator is used in different roles for the following phases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RTE Contract Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic Software Scheduler Contract Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PreBuild Data Set Contract Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic Software Scheduler Generation Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RTE Generation Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PreBuild Data Set Generation Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PostBuild Data Set Generation Phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;rte-generator-for-software-components&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#rte-generator-for-software-components&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;RTE Generator for Software-Components&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;../../../img.assets/24-11-01%E5%B5%8C%E5%85%A5%E5%BC%8F%E5%B0%8F%E6%9F%B4%E5%B8%A6%E4%BD%A0%E5%AD%A6%E4%B9%A0AutoSar%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97%E4%B8%89%E3%80%81%E6%A0%87%E5%87%86%E5%92%8C%E8%A7%84%E8%8C%83%E7%AF%87%EF%BC%884%EF%BC%89RTE/image-20241101233232600.png&#34; alt=&#34;image-20241101233232600&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;å¾ˆæ˜¾ç„¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;å…ˆæè¿° ECU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ç„¶åé€šè¿‡é…ç½®å·¥å…·é…ç½®ï¼Œæ¥ç€ç”Ÿæˆä»£ç &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;æœ€åç¼–è¯‘ä¸ºå¯æ‰§è¡Œæ–‡ä»¶&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ä¸‹é¢æ˜¯ä¸€äº› log ä¿¡æ¯&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following list is a collection of proposed information items in particular applicable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to log files used for exchanging information about errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ErrorCode&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ A symbolic name for the message text&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;StandardErrorCode&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The reference to the AUTOSAR error code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ConstraintCode&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Reference to the semantic constraint mentioned in the AUTOSAR template specification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Signature&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Signature of the message for duplicate checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Timestamp&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ A time stamp for the message&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ShortName&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ A unique identification which allows to refer to particular error messages This can also be used to establish references between error messages, e.g. for screening and also to trace back to root cause&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desc&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The human readable message text&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Component&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Such information item may help the user to locate the problem in the model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BaseUrl&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ An url for a base directory which can be used as basis for file references in a log file. This is typically the root direactory of a project structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ColumNumber&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The column of the error position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LineNumber&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The line number of the error position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LongName&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The title of the error message&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ObjectCategory&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The category of for example the involved ApplicationPrimitve DataType (e.g.VALUE)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PrimaryErrorReference&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Reference to the root cause if applicable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ScopeEntryReference&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ Reference to a scoping message if applicable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The shortName based reference to the AUTOSAR element which caused the error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ToolName&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The name of the tool which reported the error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ToolVersion&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The version of the tools which reported the error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IncidentUrl&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The Url which refers to the artifact in which the error occurs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Value&lt;/strong&gt; â€“ The actual found value which caused the problem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;rte-generator-for-basic-software-scheduler&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#rte-generator-for-basic-software-scheduler&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;RTE Generator for Basic Software Scheduler&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
